<p>ΜΝΗΣΘΗΕΛΙ<lb/>ΟΣΜΕΓΙΣΤΟΣ<lb/>ΔΕΚΟΥΡΙΩΝΚΟΛ<lb/>ΠΤΟΑΜΑΚΥΡΛΛΩ<lb/>ΥΙΩ ΕΙΛΕ <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> ΣΤΩ
                    ΜΗ<lb/>ΛΙΕΝΟΝΤΙΟΤΟΠΟΣ</p>
</div>
<div ana="b1" subtype="transcription" type="edition">
<p>Μνησθῇ Ελι<lb/>ος Μέγιστος<lb/>δεκουρίων
                        <expan>
<abbr>Κολ</abbr>
<ex>ονίας</ex>
</expan>
<expan>
<abbr>Πτο</abbr>
<ex>λεμαίδος</ex>
</expan>
<lb/>ἃμα Κυρ<supplied reason="omitted">ί</supplied>λλω<lb/>ὑιώ ΕΙΛΕ<gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
<lb/>ΣΤΩΜΗ<lb/>ΛΙΕΝΟΝΤΙ ὁ τόπος</p>
</div>
<div ana="b1" type="translation">
<p>Remembered Elios the Greatest, decurion (of the) Col(onia) Pto(lemais), with his
                    son Cyr&lt;i&gt;llus ... the place</p>
</div>
<div ana="b1" type="commentary">
<p>The last words of the inscription mean "the place" and probably refer to Elijah's
                    Cave.</p>
</div>
